                <h3 class="about">Midnight Radio</h3>
                <p>The patron saint of Midnight Radio is Caravaggio's 1605 portrait of Saint Jerome. <a href="https://www.studiointernational.com/caravaggio-a-contemporary-view-by-john-berger-vol-196-no-998-1983" target="_blank">John Berger</a> has said Caravaggio's darkness “smells of candles, over-ripe melons, damp washing to be hung out the next day.” To me, it feels like the purple-black thoughts that burble within the midnight brain.</p>
